Name: Fool
Description: Transcendence, Action without thought

Name: Mage
Description: Skill, wisdom, but also the interference of intelligence with the matter at hand

Name: High Priestess
Description: pure graciousness enters the matter

Name: Empress
Description: Love, beauty, graciousness, gentleness

Name: Emperor
Description: War, conquest, victory, ambition, stubbornness

Name: Heirophant
Description: stubborn strength, help from superiors, organization, peace

Name: Lovers
Description: Openness to inspiration, intuition, thoughtfulness divorced from practical consideration

Name: Chariot
Description: violence in maintaining traditional ideas, ruthlessness, lust for destruction

Name: Adjustment
Description: suspension of action pending decision, the act of adjustment, treaties

Name: Hermit
Description: Illumination from within, retirement from participation in current events

Name: Fortune
Description: change of fortune

Name: Lust
Description: passion, energy and action, the use of magickal power

Name: Hanged Man
Description: Enforced sacrifice, punishment, defeat

Name: Death
Description: transformation, change, logical but perhaps unexpected development of existing conditions

Name: Art
Description: combination of forces, action based on accurate calculation, escape

Name: Devil
Description: blind impulse, temptation, aching discontent, secret plan about to be executed

Name: Tower
Description: combat, ruin, destruction of plans, sudden death, escape from prison

Name: Star
Description: unexpected help, hope, realization of possibilities, dreaminess

Name: Moon
Description: deception, bewilderment, madness, brink of important change, darkest hour before dawn

Name: Sun
Description: glory, frankness, arrogance, truth

Name: Aeon
Description: taking a definitive step

Name: Universe
Description: the matter of the question itself, synthesis

Name: Knight of wands
Description: Active, generous, fierce, can also be evil minded, cruel, bigoted, brutal

Name: Queen of Wands
Description: Adaptability, steady rule, power of command, kind and generous when not opposed, but apt to turn against others without cause, obstinate and revengeful

Name: Price of Wands
Description: swift, strong, hasty, violent but just and generous. Can be cruel and intolerant

Name: Princess of Wands
Description: Brilliance, courage, sudden in anger or love, desirous of power, can be superficial, cruel and domineering

Name: 10 of Wands
Description: cruel and overbearing force applied only to material and selfish ends

Name: 9 of Wands
Description: assured recovery from illness, tremendous steady force that cannot be shaken

Name: 8 of Wands
Description: too much force applied too suddenly, violent but not lasting

Name: 7 of Wands
Description: possible victory depending on the courage exercised

Name: 6 of Wands
Description: Victory after strife, pleasure gained through labor

Name: 5 of Wands
Description: Quarreling and fighting

Name: 4 of Wands
Description: perfection or completion of a thing built up with trouble and labor

Name: 3 of Wands
Description: pride, arrogance, self assertion

Name: 2 of Wands
Description: Influence over others, authority, power, dominion

Name: Ace of Wands
Description: Natural Force (as opposed to invoked)

Name: Knight of Cups
Description: graceful, poetic, but also sensual, indolent and untruthful

Name: Queen of Cups
Description: good natured, imaginative and kind but not willing to take much trouble for another.  Very much affected by influences of others

Name: Price of Cups
Description: subtle, violent, crafty and artistic.  Powerful for good or evil, but more attracted to evil if allied with apparent wisdom or power.

Name: Princess of Cups
Description: sweet, poetic, gentle and kind.  Can be selfish, lazy and luxurious

Name: 10 of Cups
Description: permanent and lasting success and happiness

Name: 9 of Cups
Description: complete success, pleasure and happiness, wished fulfilled

Name: 8 of Cups
Description: success abandoned, decline of interest

Name: 7 of Cups
Description: slight success at outset, but not ultimately attained, promises unfulfilled

Name: 6 of Cups
Description: commencement (only) of steady increase in success or enjoyment

Name: 5 of Cups
Description: disappointment in love, marriage broken off, loss of friendship, unkindness of a friend

Name: 4 of Cups
Description: receiving pleasure or kindness (not the sexy kind), but with underlying discomfort of drawbacks

Name: 3 of Cups
Description: abundance, hospitality, passive success,

Name: 2 of Cups
Description: marriage, love, sexy times, pleasure

Name: Ace of Cups
Description: fertility, productivity, beauty, pleasure

Name: Knight of Swords
Description: Active, clever, fierce, subtle, courageous, but inclined to domineer.  Can also be deceitful and tyrannical

Name: Queen of Swords
Description: Intensely perceptive, subtle, quick and confident.  Accurate in superficial things, graceful.  Can also be deceitful, sly, cruel but with a good exterior

Name: Price of Swords
Description: full or ideas thoughts and designs, but suspicious.  Firm in friendship and enmity, careful but can be overcautious. Can be plotting, malicious, unreliable

Name: Princess of Swords
Description: wisdom, strength, acuteness, subtlety in material things. Can also be frivolous and cunning

Name: 10 of Swords
Description: Ruin, death, defeat, disruption.  Undisciplined, warring force.  Complete disruption and failure. A repeater things, given too much to unprofitable speech

Name: 9 of Swords
Description: Illness, suffering, malice, cruelty

Name: 8 of Swords
Description: narrow, restricted, petty, a prison; too much force applied to small things

Name: 7 of Swords
Description: Journey by land, and untrustworthy character.  Partial success.  Yielding when victory is in grasp as if the last reserves of strength were used up.

Name: 6 of Swords
Description: Labor, work, journey by water. Success after anxiety and trouble, self-esteem, conceit, but modesty therewith

Name: 5 of Swords
Description: Defeat, loss, malice, spite, evil-speaking. Contest finished and decided against the purpose.  A busybody and separator of friends, cruel and cowardly, thankless and unreliable

Name: 4 of Swords
Description: Convalescence, recovery from sickness, change for the better. Rest from sorrow after it is passed through

Name: 3 of Swords
Description: Unhappiness, sorrow and tears.  Sowing of discord and strife, mischief-making, deceitful in words and repetitions, the whole according to dignity

Name: 2 of Swords
Description: Quarrel made up, but with some remaining tension in relations. Actions sometime selfish, sometimes unselfish.  Contradictory, strength through suffering, pleasure after pain.

Name: Ace of Swords
Description: Invoked Force. Can invoke either divine or demonic force.  Could be used to enforce justice, or wrath  and oppression

Name: Knight of Disks
Description: Heavy, dull and material, but can be laborious, clever and patient in material matters.  Avaricious, dull, jealous, not very courageous unless assisted by other symbols

Name: Queen of Disks
Description: She is impetuous, kind; timid, charming; great hearted; intelligent, melancholy, can be capricious and foolish

Name: Prince of Disks
Description: Increase of matter.  Increases of good or evil. Practical, reliable.  Can be selfish, animal and material: stupid.  Always slow to anger but furious if roused.

Name: Princess of Disks
Description: She is generous, kind, diligent, benevolent, courageous and persevering. Can also be pitiful and wasteful.

Name: 10 of Disks
Description: Riches and wealth. Completion of material gain and fortune; but nothing beyond: as it were, at the very pinnacle of success.

Name: 9 of Disks
Description: Inheritance, much increase of goods.

Name: 8 of Disks
Description: Skill; prudence: cunning. Over careful in small things at the expense of the great. Gain of ready money in small sums

Name: 7 of Disks
Description: Unprofitable speculations and employments; little gain for much labor.  Promises of success unfulfilled

Name: 6 of Disks
Description: Success in material things, prosperity in business.

Name: 5 of Disks
Description: Loss of profession, loss of money, monetary anxiety.  Loss of money or position, trouble about material things, poverty

Name: 4 of Disks
Description: Gain of money or influence: a present.  Assured material gain

Name: 3 of Disks
Description: Business, Paid Employment, commercial transaction.  Working and constructive force, building up, realization; gain in commercial transactions, commencement of matters to be established later

Name: 2 of Disks
Description: Pleasant change, visit friends. Harmony of change.  Wandering, discontent with fixed conditions of things.  Industrious yet unreliable.  Kind but inconsistent.  Fortunate in journeying.

Name: Ace of Disks
Description: Materiality in all senses good and evil; in a sense illusionary: it shows material gain, labor, power, wealth, etc.

Name: Null House
Description: The absence of anything, the void
